website_summaries.verdict: Great off-road performance with a budget price tag. One of the best tire choices for people getting into off-roading.
pros: Large profile of the tread and lugs, in combination with the tire width, creates a larger contact patch for more surface area and traction
Spacing between the lugs allows water and mud to fall through while rolling
cons: Tread wears down unevenly over time

customer_reviews.title: 98 xj jeep, 00 xj jeep 33x12.5R15
customer_reviews.text: Love the tires. Compared them to some 35s and it seems like they were about an inch shorter. They are definitely bigger than 33s. They are some quiet tires on road. Update- 05/16/2020. One of the best tires out there for any one who loves going offroad. Had them for about a year or so they are daily driven from work to home and every weekend i put about 600 miles driving round trip from odessa tx to el paso tx. they have alot of tread still left on them. I go offroad every weekend (mostly rock and sand) and they work flawlessly. Will definitely buy for same rig or any other 4x4 vehicle

customer_reviews.title: Great large tires
customer_reviews.text: One of the best riding tires when it comes to a large mud tire. I have run many different tires from 31" to 40". I have recently replaced a set of 33" and 37" with these and there is a night/day difference. I just installed a set of 38X13 on my JKU and the ride is great and silent. Pay attention to the yellow and red dots for balancing purposes.
customer_reviews.author: Mark Kilbane

customer_reviews.title: Great off-road performance
customer_reviews.text: Took these to Rausch Creek ORP snd they did great when aired down to about 12lbs. The side walls did great, treads were good on the rocks and mud. They rode well enough on the road and for the price these are hard to beat. Can’t say much on road longevity but I bought these for off road use and not for looks or treadlife.
customer_reviews.author: Timothy K.

customer_reviews.title: Incredible tire!
customer_reviews.text: If you are on the fence about buying inexpensive 33" mudtires, don't be. These tires are everything I would expect from a $250 name brand tire. The lugs are deep which will do fine in mud and should provide plenty of life. Sometimes big mud tires are difficult to balance, but these mounted and balanced without any problems. I expected significant road noise and was suprised to find LESS road noise than the A/T tires I was running prior. Very happy with my purchase!

customer_reviews.title: Good price, durable, and versatile.

I hit the trails last weekend and they perform great. The price is relatively low, without sacrificing quality. Definitely get yourself a set.

product_meta.title: Milestar Patagonia M/T Mud-Terrain Radial Tire - 33X12.50R15 108Q
product_meta.description: For superior traction in harsh terrain, look no further than the PATAGONIA M/T off-road tire. Whether it’s rocks, mud, snow or sand the PATAGONIA M/T is one tough tire and will provide maximum traction in any terrain. Designed to be at home rock crawling, exploring the desert, mud bogging, playing in the dunes, or a casual drive through mountain trails, the PATAGONIA M/T has all the attributes to overcome any terrain. The high-void tread design is engineered to provide aggressive biting edges while promoting self-cleaning. Staggered, off-center tread blocks provide increased traction while enhancing on-the-road performance. The PATAGONIA M/T’s 3-ply sidewall provides additional protection against impact damage, while stone ejectors combat stone drilling, especially useful for rock crawling and all-terrain exploration. Built to tackle rugged terrain anywhere you may want to explore, the PATAGONIA M/T will allow you to push your vehicle to the limit. This off-road tire is available in LT and flotation sizes for both import and domestic 2X4, 4X4 and AWD vehicles.
feature_bullets: The high-void tread design is engineered to provide aggressive biting edges while promoting self cleaning
Staggered, off-centre tread blocks provide increased traction while enhancing on-the-road performance
Raised White Lettering offers a classic off-road styling to go along with off-road performance
Complex siping aids in mantaining solid control and grip under extreme on and off-road conditions
3-Ply Sidewall provides added strength and impact protection
